codex
The main execution path is worse than a normal router trust model: the relay path has no requester authorization at all, and the router/spender/data triplet is fully user-controlled. I’m validating whether that lets a relay drain approved user funds directly, and whether route accounting bugs let it spend contract-held balances too.
