I’ve confirmed there is no on-chain authorization layer for `request.executionRequest.requester`, and there is also no router/spender whitelist despite comments claiming otherwise. I’m tightening the remaining findings around the route-accounting bug and the proxy’s initialization/funding edge cases so the final report only contains distinct root causes.
